It has called for member states to urgently address all forms of discrimination, violence, marginalisation, stigmatisation and exclusion experienced in certain parts of the world by widows. They were also asked to ensure the participation of widows in decision-making processes. Other issues included registering and recognising all marriages and to ensure widows have full access to inheritance and social protection. Any barriers that impede the rights of women when it comes to the ownership or inheritance of land and property should also be eliminated, it said. --BBC--